{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/how-i-explained-word-embeddings-to-my-non-technical-colleagues-52ced76cf3bb", "time": 1683012208.778673, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/how-i-explained-word-embeddings-to-my-non-technical-colleagues-52ced76cf3bb/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "How I Explained Word Embeddings To My Non-Technical Colleagues | by GreekDataGuy | Towards Data Science", "h1": "How I Explained Word Embeddings To My Non-Technical Colleagues", "description": "Below are a few words, \u201cbright\u201d, \u201cshiny\u201d and \u201cdog\u201d, translated into numbers with popular word-embedding library, Word2Vec. When using pre-trained embeddings like Word2Vec, the numeric representation\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://medium.com/swlh/bag-of-words-in-machine-learning-13c1de579d2d", "anchor_text": "bags of words", "paragraph_index": 7}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Word2vec", "anchor_text": "Word2Vec", "paragraph_index": 9}, {"url": "https://radimrehurek.com/gensim/models/word2vec.html", "anchor_text": "some code", "paragraph_index": 26}, {"url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/No_free_lunch_theorem", "anchor_text": "no free lunch", "paragraph_index": 27}, {"url": "http://gmail.com", "anchor_text": "gmail.com", "paragraph_index": 29}], "all_paragraphs": ["What are they? What do they look like? How are they made?\u2026", "I\u2019ll break it down without code or lingo.", "This is based on my experience explaining machine learning terms to non-technical colleagues.", "You can\u2019t feed text to an ML model.", "Because, in a nutshell, math doesn\u2019t work on text.", "You must convert words/sentences/etc\u2026 to a list of numbers first.", "Word embeddings are one approach to converting text to a machine-readable format.", "There are several approaches, including bags of words, but we won\u2019t get into those here.", "Below are a few words, \u201cbright\u201d, \u201cshiny\u201d and \u201cdog\u201d, translated into numbers with popular word-embedding library, Word2Vec.", "When using pre-trained embeddings like Word2Vec, the numeric representation of each word comes included.", "You simply convert your words into each given sequence of numbers, then plug them into your model.", "But relative to each other, they contain a lot of information.", "In the previous Word2Vec example, we can see that at each index, \u201cbright\u201d and \u201cshiny\u201d are more similar to each other than to \u201cdog\u201d.", "If we plotted D1 and D2 on a 2x2 grid, we would see \u201cbright\u201d and \u201cshiny\u201d very close to each other, and \u201cdog\u201d further away.", "In the word-embedding approach, words with a similar meaning \u201cshould\u201d have similar numeric values.", "Because a word IS its context.", "\u201ccontext\u201d = \u201cthe words used around a word\u201d in the training text used to build the word-embedding.", "So when deriving numeric values for \u201cbeautiful\u201d and \u201cgorgeous\u201d we would likely find similar words around them, and they would get similar numeric values.", "A word\u2019s numeric values are a function of the weights in a neural network upon correctly guessing a word, given its context (CBOW approach).", "The neural network keeps adjusting its weights until it can take the context of a word, and guess the word itself.", "At that point, the current weights (think knobs and dials on a machine) become the numeric values.", "Similar context is often found around words with similar meaning.", "So similar neural network weights will predict similar words.", "Disclaimer: I\u2019ve made some generalizations and skipped some small steps to help make this more explainability", "Word embeddings are an approach (one of several) for converting text into numbers so computers can process it.", "Practical experience (successes and failures) is your best guide as to when you should actually use them, versus other approaches. While very popular, they often underperform more traditional approaches (in my anecdotal experience).", "That\u2019s why I always recommend diving in and getting your hands dirty on some code.", "Remember that in machine learning, there is no free lunch. We really don\u2019t know what works until we try it!", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes.", "Just a developer. Contact: greek.data.guy \u201cat\u201d gmail.com"], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F52ced76cf3bb&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-explained-word-embeddings-to-my-non-technical-colleagues-52ced76cf3bb&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-explained-word-embeddings-to-my-non-technical-colleagues-52ced76cf3bb&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "Write"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/search?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fhow-i-explained-word-embeddings-to-my-non-technical-colleagues-52ced76cf3bb&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----